    "user": "U2M0WUZ7A",
    "text": "<@U3173MK8U> something like this.\nIn onClick:\n```\n@Override\npublic void onClick(View v) {\n    int pos = getAdapterPosition();\n    if (selectedItems.get(getAdapterPosition(),false)) {\n        selectedItems.delete(pos);\n    } else {\n        selectedItems.put(pos, true);\n    }\n    adapter.notifyItemChanged(pos);\n}\n```\nIn onBindViewHolder:\n```\n@Override\npublic void onBindViewHolder(YoutubeVideoViewHolder holder, int position) {\n    if (youtubeVideos.size() == 0) {\n        if (itemSpinner != null) {\n            itemSpinner.setVisibility(View.GONE);\n        }\n    }\n    if (position != youtubeVideos.size()) {\n        holder.bindVideo(youtubeVideos.get(position), videoDetailResponses.get(position));\n    }\n    backgroundView.setSelected(selectedItems.get(position));\n}\n```\n\nBy the way, Spinner in Android is a ComboBox, not a ProgressBar.",
